# ShadcnUI Rules

## Core Principles
- Install ShadcnUI components in `@vencura/ui` (packages/ui)
- Always import from `@vencura/ui/components/*`, never directly from packages/ui
- All Radix UI primitives must be imported from `@vencura/ui/radix`; never import any `@radix-ui/react-*` packages directly in apps or other packages
- Update Tailwind preset/tokens in packages/ui (not per app)
- Application-specific components go in app's `components` folder
- Hooks and utils must be collocated with components (same directory)

## Installation Pattern
Components installed in `packages/ui/src/components/`. Each app's `components.json` points to:
- `"utils": "@vencura/ui/lib/utils"`
- `"ui": "@vencura/ui/components"`

## Import Patterns
```tsx
import { Button } from "@vencura/ui/components/button"
import { cn } from "@vencura/ui/lib/utils"
```

## Component Patterns
Use class-variance-authority (cva) pattern for variants and `cn` utility for merging class names:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@vencura/ui/lib/utils"
import { cva } from "class-variance-authority"

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "rounded-md font-medium transition-colors",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-white hover:bg-primary/90",
        secondary: "bg-secondary text-white hover:bg-secondary/90"
      }
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default"
    }
  }
)
```

## Design System Organization
- Core UI components in `@vencura/ui`
- Application-specific components in app's `components` folder
- Hooks and utils collocated with components

## Mobile-First Design
All components follow mobile-first responsive design. See [Mobile-First Rules](./mobile-first.mdc) for guidelines.
